# No Empty Styled Components

## Core Rule

- **NEVER create styled components with empty template literals** (`styled.div\`\``)
- Empty styled components add unnecessary overhead and provide no value
- Use regular HTML elements, React fragments, or remove the wrapper entirely

## When to Remove

<example type="invalid">
// ❌ Bad: Empty styled component
const Container = styled.div``

// Usage
<Container>
<Content />
</Container>
</example>

<example>
// ✅ Good: Use regular element if wrapper is needed
<div>
  <Content />
</div>
</example>

<example>
// ✅ Good: Use fragment if no wrapper needed
<>
  <Content />
</>
</example>

<example>
// ✅ Good: Remove wrapper entirely if not needed
<Content />
</example>

## Guidelines

- If a styled component has no styles, remove it
- Use regular HTML elements (`div`, `span`, etc.) if a wrapper is needed for structure
- Use React fragments (`<>...</>`) if grouping is needed without a DOM element
- Only create styled components when you actually need to apply styles
